.TH READSEEK 1 "2026-06-13" "readseek 0.1.6" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
readseek \- structural source reader with stable line hashes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B readseek
[\fB\-h\fR]
[\fB\-V\fR]
.P
.B readseek
\fBfile\fR
[\fB--language=\fR\fIlanguage\fR]
\fItarget\fR
.P
.B readseek
\fBread\fR
[\fB--start=\fR\fIline\fR]
[\fB--end=\fR\fIline\fR]
[\fB--offset=\fR\fIline\fR]
[\fB--limit=\fR\fIn\fR]
[\fB--language=\fR\fIlanguage\fR]
\fItarget\fR
.P
.B readseek
\fBmap\fR
[\fB--language=\fR\fIlanguage\fR]
\fItarget\fR
.P
.B readseek
\fBsymbol\fR
[\fB--language=\fR\fIlanguage\fR]
\fItarget\fR
[\fIaddress\fR]
.P
.B readseek
\fBsearch\fR
[\fB-c\fR|\fB--cached\fR]
[\fB-o\fR|\fB--others\fR]
[\fB-i\fR|\fB--ignored\fR]
[\fB--language=\fR\fIlanguage\fR]
\fItarget\fR
\fIpattern\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B readseek
reads source files and emits JSON for language detection, line-hash addressed
reads, structural source maps, symbol reads, and AST pattern searches. It is
intended for scripts and coding agents that need stable references to source
locations.
.P
All command output is JSON.
.SS Targets
A
.I target
is a file path. It may include a one-based line number or a 3-character line
hash suffix in the form
.I file:line
or
.IR file:hash .
.P
For
.BR symbol ,
the target may also include a symbol address or unqualified symbol name in the
form
.IR file:symbol .
.P
Line hashes are the 3-character hashes shown in
.BR read ,
.BR map ,
and
.B search
output.
.SS Languages
.B readseek
detects supported languages from file names, extensions, shebangs, and syntax
metadata. Use
.B --language
when a file is ambiguous or has no useful extension. The override accepts the
built-in language identifiers and aliases; unsupported text files are reported
as
.BR unknown .
.SS Commands
.TP
.B file
Emit target file detection information: language, support status, binary
status, MIME type, and syntax name.
.TP
.B read
Emit a target file range with line numbers, 3-character line hashes, and text.
.TP
.B map
Emit a structural source map with each symbol kind, name, address, start and
end lines, and boundary line hashes.
.TP
.B symbol
Emit the source range for a mapped symbol. Select the symbol by address
argument, target symbol suffix, or target line/hash suffix.
.TP
.B search
Run an AST pattern against a file or every supported source file below a
directory. Unparseable files are skipped.
.P
Directory searches inside Git repositories use Git-style file selection by
default: tracked files plus untracked, non-ignored files. Search output is
grouped by file and includes file hashes, matches, captures, boundary line
hashes, and hashlines for matched ranges.
.SS Options
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB--help\fR
Print help and exit.
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB--version\fR
Print version and exit.
.TP
\fB--language=\fR\fIlanguage\fR
Override language detection for commands that parse source text. This is useful
for extensionless files, generated files, or ambiguous syntax.
.TP
\fB--start=\fR\fIline\fR
First one-based line to include for
.BR read .
.TP
\fB--end=\fR\fIline\fR
Last one-based line to include for
.BR read .
.TP
\fB--offset=\fR\fIline\fR
Alias for
.BR --start .
.TP
\fB--limit=\fR\fIn\fR
Maximum number of lines to include for
.BR read .
.TP
\fB-c\fR, \fB--cached\fR
For
.BR search
on a directory inside a Git repository, search tracked/indexed files.
.TP
\fB-o\fR, \fB--others\fR
For
.BR search
on a directory inside a Git repository, search untracked non-ignored files.
.TP
\fB-i\fR, \fB--ignored\fR
For
.BR search
with
.BR --others ,
include ignored untracked files. Outside Git repositories, Git file selection
flags are ignored and directory search falls back to normal recursive traversal.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B READSEEK_CACHE_DIR
Override the base cache directory. When set,
.B readseek
stores the source map cache below
.IR READSEEK_CACHE_DIR/readseek .
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
0
Success.
.TP
1
Operational error, such as a missing file, unsupported binary file, malformed
input, cache error, or symbol lookup failure.
.TP
2
Usage error.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I readseek/cache.sqlite3
Source map cache below
.B READSEEK_CACHE_DIR
or the platform cache directory.
.TP
.I ${XDG_CACHE_HOME:-~/.cache}/readseek/cache.sqlite3
Typical Linux cache location.
.SH EXAMPLES
Detect a file:
.br
.B "  readseek file src/main.rs"
.P
Read lines 10 through 20:
.br
.B "  readseek read src/main.rs --start 10 --end 20"
.P
Read a file around a target line:
.br
.B "  readseek read src/main.rs:42 --limit 12"
.P
Build a structural map:
.br
.B "  readseek map src/main.rs"
.P
Read a symbol by target suffix:
.br
.B "  readseek symbol src/main.rs:run"
.P
Read the symbol containing a line:
.br
.B "  readseek symbol src/main.rs:270"
.P
Search with an explicit language override:
.br
.B "  readseek search src 'int $NAME() { return $VALUE; }' --language cpp"
.P
Search tracked files in a Git repository:
.br
.B "  readseek search -c src 'fn $NAME() { $$$BODY }' --language rust"
.P
Search untracked files, including ignored files:
.br
.B "  readseek search -o -i . 'fn $NAME() { $$$BODY }' --language rust"
.SH BUILDING
See
.B README.md
in the source distribution for build instructions.
